verbose_text: Cyclic RGD peptide modification promotes the selective bonding of nanoparticles to tumor blood vessels (via a v beta 3, a v beta 5 and a 5 beta 1 integrin receptors overexpressed by activated endothelial cells), and the nanoparticles were further modified with DOTA to enable 64 Cu complexation and simultaneous PET-MRI monitoring.
